Introduction

This document generates figures and tables for Joes Klebsiella genomics paper.

MLST, K and O loci

read_tsv("~/Documents/Sanger/DASSIM3/data_processed/ariba_mlst/DASSIM3_mlst_summary.tsv") %>% 
  filter(ST != "ST") %>% 
  mutate(ST = gsub("\\*", "", ST)) %>%
  select(ST, lane) -> mlst

read_tsv("~/Documents/Sanger/DASSIM3/data_processed/kleborate/kleborate.all.txt") %>% 
  mutate(strain = gsub("\\.contigs_spades","",strain)) %>% 
  filter(ST != "ST") %>% 
  mutate(type = "DASSIM") %>% 
  select(-ST) %>% 
  left_join(
    mlst,
    by = c("strain" = "lane")) ->
  kleborate

malawi_lanes_include <- read_lines(here("data_raw/malawi_context_lanes_retaines_following_qc.txt"))

read_tsv(here("data_raw/all_malawi_context_assemblies_kleborate_output.txt")) %>% 
  mutate(strain = gsub("\\.contigs_velvet","",strain)) %>% 
  filter(strain %in% malawi_lanes_include) %>% 
  mutate(type = "context") -> kleborate2
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   .default = col_character(),
##   contig_count = col_double(),
##   N50 = col_double(),
##   largest_contig = col_double(),
##   total_size = col_double(),
##   virulence_score = col_double()
## )
## See spec(...) for full column specifications.
kleborate %>% 
  group_by(ST) %>% 
  mutate(n = n(),
         ST = paste0("ST",ST)) %>% 
  filter(n > 1, ST != "STNovel") %>%  
  ggplot(aes(fct_infreq(ST))) +
  geom_bar(fill = viridis_pal()(4)[3]) +
  coord_flip() + 
  labs(y = "Number", x = element_blank()) +
  theme_bw()  -> a

kleborate %>% 
  group_by(K_locus) %>% 
  mutate(n = n()) %>% 
  filter(n > 1) %>%  
  ggplot(aes(fct_infreq(K_locus))) +
  geom_bar(fill = viridis_pal()(4)[2]) +
  coord_flip()  +
  labs(y = "Number", x = element_blank()) +
  theme_bw()  -> b

kleborate %>% 
  mutate(O_locus = 
           case_when(
             grepl("O1", O_locus) ~ "O1",
             grepl("O2", O_locus) ~ "O2",
             TRUE ~ O_locus)
  ) %>% 
  group_by(O_locus) %>% 
  mutate(n = n()) %>% 
 # filter(n > 1) %>%  
  ggplot(aes(fct_infreq(O_locus))) +
  geom_bar(fill = viridis_pal()(4)[1]) +
  coord_flip() +
  labs(y = "Number", x = element_blank()) +
  theme_bw()  -> c

# cum K and O serotypes
bind_rows(
  kleborate %>%
    group_by(K_locus) %>%
    summarise(n = n()) %>%
    ungroup() %>%
    arrange(desc(n)) %>%
    mutate(
      n_loci = 1:n(),
      cum_n = cumsum(n),
      cum_prop = cum_n / max(cum_n),
      type = "K-type"
    ) %>% 
    rename(Locus = K_locus),
  kleborate %>%
      mutate(O_locus = 
           case_when(
             grepl("O1", O_locus) ~ "O1",
             grepl("O2", O_locus) ~ "O2",
             TRUE ~ O_locus)
  ) %>% 
    group_by(O_locus) %>%
    summarise(n = n()) %>%
    ungroup() %>%
    arrange(desc(n)) %>%
    mutate(
      n_loci = 1:n(),
      cum_n = cumsum(n),
      cum_prop = cum_n / max(cum_n),
      type = "O-type"
    ) %>% 
    rename(Locus = O_locus),
  kleborate %>%
    filter(ST != "Novel")  %>% 
    group_by(ST) %>%
    summarise(n = n()) %>%
    ungroup() %>%
    arrange(desc(n)) %>%
    mutate(
      n_loci = 1:n(),
      cum_n = cumsum(n),
      cum_prop = cum_n / max(cum_n),
      type = "ST"
    ) %>% 
    rename(Locus = ST)
) %>% 
  mutate(type = factor(type, levels = 
                         c("O-type",
                           "K-type",
                           "ST"))) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(n_loci, cum_prop, color = type)) +
  geom_line() +
  theme_bw() +
  scale_color_manual(values = viridis_pal()(4)[1:3]) +
  labs(x= "Number of K/O-type/ST", y = "Cum. prevalence") + 
  theme(legend.title = element_blank()) -> d
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
(a + b + (c / d)) + plot_annotation(tag_levels = "A") -> stplot

stplot

FIGURE X: Diversity of Klebsiella chromasomal sequence type (ST, A), K-type (B) and O-type (C). (D) shows cumulative prevalence for ST, K-type and O-types for all isolates in the collection as a function of the number of K-types, O-types, or STs, with each category ordered in size from largest to smallest. 

ggsave(filename = here("manuscript/kleb/figures/F1_stplot.svg"),plot = stplot,
       width =11,

AMR determinents

amr.ariba <- read_csv("~/Documents/Sanger/DASSIM3/data_processed/ariba/DASSIM3-ariba-report.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   .default = col_character()
## )
## See spec(...) for full column specifications.
# get beta lactamase phenotype and tidy -------------------------------------

bls <- read_tsv(
  "https://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pathogen/betalactamases/Allele.tab"
  )
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   `#allele name` = col_character(),
##   `protein accession #` = col_character(),
##   `nucleotide accession #` = col_character(),
##   `gene name` = col_character(),
##   start = col_double(),
##   stop = col_double(),
##   strand = col_character(),
##   `curated gene product name` = col_character()
## )
bls %>% 
  rename_with(~ tolower(gsub(" ", "_", .x))) %>% 
  rename_with(~ gsub("#", "", .x)) %>% 
  mutate(allele_name = gsub("-", "_", allele_name),
         class = case_when(
           grepl("carbapenem-hydrolyzing", 
                 curated_gene_product_name) ~ "CPE",
           grepl("metallo-beta-lactamase", 
                 curated_gene_product_name) ~ "CPE",
           grepl("extended-spectrum beta-lactamase", 
                 curated_gene_product_name) ~ "ESBL",
           grepl("class C", 
                 curated_gene_product_name) ~ "AmpC",
           grepl("beta-lactamase", 
                 curated_gene_product_name) ~ "Penicillinase"
         )) -> 
  bls
